\'93You hypocrite, don\'92t sit there whining at me.\uc0\u8232 Among the gods who live on Mount Olympus, \'97[890]\u8232 you\'92re the one I hate the most. For you love war,\'a0\'a00\u8232 constant strife and battle. Your mother, Hera,\u8232 has an implacable, unyielding spirit.\u8232 It\'92s hard for me to control how she reacts\u8232 to what I say. You\'92re suffering because of her,\u8232 through her conniving, that\'92s what I think.\u8232 But I\'92ll leave you in pain no longer.\u8232 You\'92re my child\'97your mother and I made you.\u8232 But if you\'92d been born from any other god,\u8232 by now you\'92d be lower than the sons\u8232 of Ouranos\'97you\'92re so destructive.\'940\
